# Identifier Convention

- Use `publicId` (nanoid) for public resource identifiers (route params and external-facing entity ids).
- Use `id` (UUID) for internal database identity.
- Fields like `profileId`, `userId`, `talkLangageId`, etc. are foreign keys and represent internal table `id` values (UUID), not `publicId`.
- Keep existing variable names used by the project; do not rename identifiers unless explicitly requested.
- Never expose internal root entity `id` as the public identifier of a resource.
